    "recap_headline": "University of Houston Athletics",
    "recap_text": "HOUSTON \u2013\nThe Houston Baseball team trounced Rice in the first game of the Silver Glove Series, hitting three homers while holding the Owls to just three hits at Don Sanders Field at Darryl and Lori Schroeder Park Tuesday night.\nFreshman\nCaden Cooper\n(1-0) picked up his first career win, tossing 5.1 shutout innings while fanning two. He led a Houston (11-5) pitching staff that ceded just three hits and one run against Rice (9-8). Jeremiah Arnett (2-1) took the loss for the Owls, allowing five runs (three earned) on eight hits and a walk.\nPLAYER HIGHLIGHTS\nJustin Cherrington\n: 1-2, HR, 4 RBI, R\nXavier Perez\n: 1-4, HR, 3 RBI, 2 R, HBP\nJackson LaLima\n: 3-5, 2 2B, RBI, R\nCarsten Sabathia III\n: 1-4, HR, 2 R, 2 RBI\nAlex Solis\n: 1.2 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 0 BB, 1 K\nNOTABLES\nHouston has won the last seven games against Rice and picked up its 25\nth\nwin against the Owls under Head Coach\nTodd Whitting\n.\nThe Cougars have scored double-digit runs in each of the last four games against Rice, outscoring the Owls 56-12 over that span.\nSophomore\nJustin Cherrington\nhit the team's second grand slam of the season.\nThe 12-run win is Houston's largest win since last year's Silver Glove Series, when the Cougars defeated Rice 15-3 on April 15, 2025.\nThe first run of the game marked the 21,000\nth\nrun in program history.\nKEY INNINGS\n1\nst\n| Houston struck first, wasting no time as redshirt sophomore\nXavier Perez\nlaunched a two-run homer in the second at-bat of the game to take a 2-0 lead.\n3\nrd\n| The Cougars added another pair of runs in the third. With a pair of runners in scoring position, freshman\nBlake Fields\ndrove in senior\nDylan Maxcey\nwith a sac-fly. Senior\nCarsten Sabathia III\nscored in the next at-bat as sophomore\nJackson LaLima\nhit his second double of the game to push the lead to four.\n4\nth\n| Maxcey hit the Cougars second sac-fly of the game in the fourth to score senior\nTyler Cox\n, making the score 5-0. Sabathia III added another pair of runs to the tally immediately after, hitting his fifth homer of the season to extend the edge to seven.\n5\nth\n| Two walks and a single loaded the bases for Houston in the bottom of the fifth and Perez picked up his third RBI of the contest with a fielder's choice that scored freshman\nPeyton Dickens\n.\n8\nth\n| While Rice got on the board with a lone run in the top of the inning, Houston sealed the run-rule win with a five-spot in the home half of the frame. A double, walk and single filled the bases again for Houston and senior\nCarter Sintek\ndrew a walk to force a run home. Cherrington crushed a 430-foot grand slam to left to end the game immediately after, walking off the Owls and locking in a 13-1 win.\nUP NEXT\nHouston starts Big 12 Conference play this weekend as it hosts Kansas State for a three-game series at Schroeder Park. The slate starts at 6:30 p.m., Friday, before continuing at 6:30 p.m., Saturday and concluding at 1 p.m. on Sunday.\nSUPPORT THE COUGARS\nFans can make a direct impact on the success of Houston Baseball by\nproviding NIL opportunities\nand by\njoining the Dugout Club\nwhich provides financial support directly to Houston Baseball for needs beyond its operating budget.\nSTAY CONNECTED\nFans can receive updates by following\n@UHCougarBB\non X, formerly known as Twitter, and catch up with the latest news and notes on the team by clicking LIKE on the team's Facebook page at\nHouston Cougar Baseball\n. Fans can also follow the team on Instagram at\n@uhcougarbb\n.\n\u2013 UHCougars.com \u2013"
  },
